From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 22:06:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Massive expansion: exhaustive intel dump, 11 C2 exploit
 attacks, 5 new scan vectors
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Intel dump per finding now includes:
- Full /proc/status: Name, State, PPid, Uid, Gid, NStgid, NSpid, VmSize, VmRSS, Threads
- Process start time (computed from boot + jiffies)
- Open FD breakdown: socket/file/pipe counts
- Environment flags: LD_PRELOAD, LD_LIBRARY_PATH, LD_AUDIT detection
- Per-PID network connections with state (ESTABLISHED/LISTEN/TIME_WAIT etc)
- Executable metadata: size, mtime, mode, uid
- File findings: inode, all 3 timestamps (mtime/atime/ctime), uid/gid, mode

C2 exploit arsenal (11 real protocol-level attacks):
[1] Binary flood — 64KB protocol state corruption
[2] HTTP resource exhaustion — huge Content-Length + partial body
[3] TLS record corruption — fake ClientHello with impossible lengths + alert
[4] Length-prefix integer overflow — 0x7FFFFFFF/0xFFFFFFFF/signed overflow
[5] IRC command flood — NICK/JOIN/QUIT spam for IRC-based C2
[6] Fake bot registration — pollute C2 bot database with 16 garbage bots
[7] RST storm — 64 rapid connect/RST to exhaust connection handling
[8] Slowloris — hold 32 connections open with slow partial headers
[9] HTTP pipeline abuse — 200 pipelined requests without reading
[10] Cobalt Strike frame confusion — fake CS beacon metadata frames
[11] Metasploit TLV confusion — fake meterpreter session frames

Each attack reports success/fail with bytes sent. Summary shows landed/total.

New scan vectors:
- /etc/ld.so.preload — rootkit shared library injection
- /etc/rc.local — boot persistence with wget/curl/base64/nohup
- SSH authorized_keys — forced command backdoor detection
- systemd service units — ExecStart pointing to /tmp or using curl/wget

1626 lines, up from 1121. Zero warnings.
